-- CMS to pay $200 mln to settle shareholder suits
-- 
-- Fri Jan 5, 2007 10:09am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/05/cms-shareholder-idUSWEN184220070105

 

 NEW YORK  Jan 5 (Reuters) - CMS Energy said on Friday it
reached a preliminary agreement to pay $200 million to settle
shareholder class action lawsuits related to fake trades made
by a former Texas subsidiary in 2000-2002. 

   The company also said it would pay a net $12 million to
Duke/Fluor Daniel after an arbitration panel's ruling on a
dispute concerning the construction of the Dearborn Industrial
Generation Facility.  ( CMS.N )


